SIMPLE: hyponitrous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyponitrous
<hw>Hy`po*ni"trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + <ets>nitrous</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Containing or derived from nitrogen having a lower valence than in
nitrous compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hyponitrous acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
unstable nitrogen acid, <chform>NOH</chform>, whose salts are produced
by reduction of the nitrates, although the acid itself is not isolated
in the free state except as a solution in water; -- called also
<altname>nitrosylic acid</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hyponym</ent>⟦br⟧
